text: Tried the mala, which is quite a disappointment as well as the Tissue Prata (with chocolate), not too bad, but little bit too salty for the crust. Yet to try other stalls but from these 2 food stalls, will say it is quite standard. Gonna update when tried other stalls!
The lousy chicken rice shop! 2*$4.5 per chicken leg and $7 chicken breast. Plus a vegetable costs me $21.4! The worst chicken rice ever had in Singapore!

Toast bread with butter and kaya..$1.40 two slices.. Worst i have eaten. Thin butter and no taste or colour kaya. Not to come again.  Waste my stomach space.
Old man serving coffee super nice. Only compliment.

Nice spacious coffee shop that is next to sheng siong and LRT layar. Table and chairs are not the normal that get you from coffeeshop but they are using wooden tables and chairs that add ambience to the place. The econ been hoon stall is the most popular and has the longest queue. Coffee and tea are nice but cost 10cents more per cup as compared to other coffeeshops
First time trying the fried Hokkien mee. Was surprised that it's so nice as there's no queue. Bought the $6 plate, quite a generous serving and the chilli is good.
